reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect replacement part
reviews.reviewText: This was an easy replacement of the OE lamps on my 2005 Dodge Ram. It has an external resistor that had to be plugged in and zip tied to the harness, but it works perfectly and really lights up the license plate a lot better than the stock fixtures and incandescent bulbs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Replacement for older Rams
reviews.reviewText: There are no instructions for how to replace/install these lights. I found a how to video on youtube to help walk me through installation. The clips were my biggest struggle. I'd recommend buying new spring clips before starting. My truck is a 2017 and the clips were nearly unusable. They were rotten enough that they lacked any spring or temper. These lights are much brighter than the originals.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A serviceable replacement
reviews.reviewText: These replacement lamps were relatively easy to install. While underneath the vehicle you can see where the light penetrates the bumper. Just forward of the light there is a small lip that is attached to a clip that secures the light. Pry the clip toward the front of the vehicle and the light will be freed and can be removed from above. Obviously you will have to unplug it first. Set the new light in the opening. Then plug the resistor into the old plug and new light. The clip will go into the cavity between the bumper and a piece of reinforcement. Slide the clip back making sure to engage both the bottom and top of the new light. Secure the resistor and loose wires with a few zip ties.I think the kit included zip ties but I'd recommend buying new spring clips before starting. My truck is a 2015 and the clips were nearly unusable. They were rotten enough that they lacked any spring or temper.These lights are much brighter than the originals. The light is slightly blue but it doesn't bother me. Remember you could alternatively just replace the 194 bulbs in the existing housing with LEDs but they would not be nearly as bright

reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not the same size
reviews.reviewText: The lights are a bit smaller than the OEM. They also don't come with the securing brackets, so hold onto your OEM ones

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Bright but fragile
reviews.reviewText: These are nice plate lamps but the plastic tabs on the back are fragile. I broke one trying to install with the new supplied clips. I ended having to use my old clips on the other side and I had to use screws to secure the broken side. Frustrating to say the least.
